Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.42,0:00:18.40,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.10,0:00:36.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.06,0:00:47.90,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:56.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.76,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:20.66,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:26.50,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.30,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.10,0:00:36.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.06,0:00:47.90,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:56.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.76,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:20.66,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:26.50,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.30,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.10,0:01:50.04,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,270)}Ep. 01 - To a New Land
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.46,0:02:16.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Mother, let's have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:22.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Mary. You aren't hiding anything from me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.55,0:02:26.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have nothing to hide from you, mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.45,0:02:30.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there really any news?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.26,0:02:32.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,News?﻿
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.35,0:02:36.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Half a year passed since Arthur left the village with my grandchildren.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.33,0:02:40.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's been seven months, even.\NIt happened last August.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.90,0:02:41.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.87,0:02:46.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The letter of them arriving to Australia was supposed to come long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.49,0:02:51.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother! Did I not tell you\NEngland and Australia are very far apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.88,0:02:56.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The one is on the edge of the Earth for the other.\NIt's more than three months of sailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.52,0:02:58.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You keep saying that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:06.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I only hope we receive some news soon\Nof them arriving safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.93,0:03:15.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like my husband is back. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.25,0:03:19.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿He's been to the town, right?\NI hope he stopped by the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:20.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:24.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The snow definitely piles up tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.95,0:03:28.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿You didn't put the horse into the stable?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.55,0:03:32.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I will, of course.\NBut before that, I wanted to give this to your mother. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.29,0:03:38.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the long-awaited letter from Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.51,0:03:40.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:51.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.23,0:03:58.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Read it for me, Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.78,0:04:00.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm too afraid of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.85,0:04:03.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think there's anything to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.61,0:04:06.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It was Clara who wrote this letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.82,0:04:10.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿She turned sixteen while on board the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.49,0:04:14.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm reading, mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:20.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿"Grandma, aunt Mary, and finally, uncle Fred, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.13,0:04:24.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our family made it safely to Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.47,0:04:30.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We spent ninety five days aboard,\Nuntil we could finally tread the soil again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:34.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, we've been trapped\Nin the confined cabin for over three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.65,0:04:40.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To decide who is getting ferried ashore first, we drew lots." 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.45,0:04:43.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Boat is all ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.24,0:04:45.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Okay! Next group, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:47.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That would be us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.17,0:04:51.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, sis.\NI'll lend you a shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.57,0:04:52.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Thank you, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.47,0:04:53.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're waiting. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.96,0:04:56.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our family goes ashore first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.01,0:05:01.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Mr. Pettywell, but according\Nto the lots we've drawn before, it's our turn now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:06.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿My wife's health is deteriorating.\NShe cannot wait for her turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.39,0:05:07.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Now, let us go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:10.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So is my daughter's health.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.83,0:05:13.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My family is different from yours. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.16,0:05:16.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I paid a fortune to board this ship and get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:19.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I also did that for my wife and my servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:23.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have a privilege over those\Nwho came here on government expense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:25.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:27.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:29.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't forget anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:43.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... Can't be helped.\NWe'll wait for the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.53,0:05:44.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿What a rotten person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.69,0:05:45.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Kate...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:05:48.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm saying it because Mr. Pettywell\Nreally is a rotten person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.69,0:05:50.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.43,0:05:52.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Be quiet, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:57.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What now? He queue-jumped in front of us.\NSo puffed up! You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.40,0:06:06.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really surprised Marsh didn't die in there! 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:09.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why would he be dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.37,0:06:14.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You should know it just as well!\NHamsters hibernate during winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.02,0:06:18.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back in England, the winter is in full swing already.\NBut here it's summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.79,0:06:23.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Therefore, Marsh cannot hibernate and it drives him crazy, I reckon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.05,0:06:27.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Marsh will be fine!\NAustralia can reinvigorate anyone! 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:32.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling better, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.14,0:06:36.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you.\NSome sea breeze reaches me even down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:40.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did shouldn't have yielded our turn to that Mr. Pettywell!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.65,0:06:43.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped.\NHe's rich after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.49,0:06:47.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what we came\Nto Southern Australia for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:51.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad said this is the land of freedom and equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.37,0:07:02.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Unfortunately, on the day of arrival,\NI wasn't in perfect health.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.57,0:07:05.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It must've been the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.84,0:07:12.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, everyone else was in high spirits. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:16.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Especially Kate and Lucy-May,\Nwho were feeling {\i1}too{\i0} good, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.85,0:07:21.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Overly enthusiastic about riding a boat,\NLucy-May tripped into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:27.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The one who rescued her\Nwas a young sailor named John.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.90,0:07:32.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the voyage,\Nhe had been the most cordial to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:35.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost summer in these parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.74,0:07:40.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, Lucy-May didn't catch a cold\Nafter tumbling into the sea."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:44.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Say, what is she talking about, Mary?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:45.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿What, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.84,0:07:51.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here it's snowing all over the place, but in Australia they have summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.85,0:07:56.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, winter and summer periods in Australia\Nare reversed in regard to England.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.36,0:07:57.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.46,0:07:59.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿It's on the southern side of the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.33,0:08:02.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How does the southern side explain the seasons reversed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:06.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, even I don't have all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.05,0:08:09.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh! Winter and summer are reversed, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.90,0:08:11.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.31,0:08:15.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least the ship didn't sink on the way.\NI was so worried it would!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.88,0:08:20.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But the hard times only start now.\N﻿They are now in a virtually uninhabited place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.75,0:08:23.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Everyone would have to blaze\Ntheir own trail from here on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:28.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Build lodgings and eventually towns.\NThen there are fields and pastures...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:33.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And worst of all, I won't see\Nmy adorable grandchildren ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:38.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey! Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.97,0:08:45.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You two! Didn't I tell you to sit tight? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.61,0:08:57.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You two just don't know how to behave, do you?\NThis time, no one is helping if you fall in the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:58.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Right, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.32,0:08:59.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.15,0:09:00.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you cold, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.46,0:09:03.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not one bit! 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:10.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh dried up already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.77,0:09:14.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Those girls have not changed one bit\Nfrom what they were back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.07,0:09:15.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Buoyant as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.97,0:09:18.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only a bit worried about Clara. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.27,0:09:22.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿By the way, what are we to do after we go ashore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.44,0:09:25.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start by arranging\Nthe sleeping quarters in the vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.15,0:09:28.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, look yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.54,0:09:30.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There are camps all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.66,0:09:36.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um... ﻿Is that place - Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.19,0:09:40.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿No, the city itself seems to be distanced from the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.16,0:09:44.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Southern Australia's capital is Adelaide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.16,0:09:49.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Even though it's the capital,\Nit has no more than 300 residents for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:12.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Thank yon, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.61,0:10:29.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On this land, we'll spend the rest of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.63,0:10:31.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.59,0:10:38.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Feels great!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.92,0:10:41.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So much fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.31,0:10:44.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿It's Australia!\NIt's Australia for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.03,0:10:52.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone! Take whatever you can carry\Nand unload it on top of that dune.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.82,0:10:53.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.14,0:10:59.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Father, when are we retrieving\Nthe rest of our things from the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.16,0:11:01.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:06.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is only the bulky stuff,\Nso the boat will have to make several trips.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.55,0:11:12.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be seeing you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:14.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.05,0:11:21.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't exert yourself since you have a fever.\NJust watch over Tob and our luggage over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:23.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.62,0:11:55.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"The scenery around us was surprisingly even more desolate than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.66,0:12:02.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help wondering\Nif humans can live in a place like that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.37,0:12:05.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I have to do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.34,0:12:08.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma, from now on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:13.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to send you a letter\Nwhenever there's a ship returning to England.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.62,0:12:15.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take care and goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:25.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,November 7th, 1837,\Nfrom Southern Australia. Clara Popple."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:35.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They have summer over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.94,0:12:45.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Now, hold it tight, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.25,0:12:45.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.41,0:12:47.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.53,0:13:02.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a skilled handyman, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:06.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Farmers have to be jacks of all trades.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.47,0:13:13.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where did mom go to fetch the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:25.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿This place is like a birds' kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.65,0:13:57.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.63,0:13:58.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.93,0:14:14.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, over there!\NMr. Pettywell is building himself a house. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.52,0:14:20.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, drive it in a bit more and that should do.\NNow, start stretching it on this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.53,0:14:23.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He could do some work himself,\Nnot just give orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.65,0:14:25.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿We've not been doing any work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.18,0:14:30.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good point. How about we stop loitering around\Nand offer some help to dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:34.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still small, so I should be allowed\Nto play around. But if you would help him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.69,0:14:38.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Not happening! If I'm going to do any work,\Nyou're doing it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.36,0:14:42.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that's enough.\NStart carrying our things into the tent, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:42.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:42.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.46,0:14:46.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, you rascals! Hurry up!\NThe sun will set soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:03.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.33,0:15:17.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you looking idly at me, you blockheads?!\NStart rebuilding it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.80,0:15:22.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Until the tent is set, no one's getting their meal!\NGet to work, you slacking breed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:29.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, what are you doing here?\NI have been looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:30.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.05,0:15:32.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There... There!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.98,0:15:35.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then "Slam!" Like that! 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.97,0:15:53.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! No playing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:59.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿I'm not playing around.\NJust making sure it doesn't hurt when you use it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.01,0:16:04.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't hurt, doesn't hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.05,0:16:07.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You fool! 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.30,0:16:10.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't hurt, doesn't hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.59,0:16:18.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What a great smell!\NI'm so hungry it drives me crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:19.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:23.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:28.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Please wait just a bit longer.\N﻿The salt pork soup is on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.00,0:16:30.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just needs some more seething.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.04,0:16:34.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, we've laid enough straw in the tent.\NYou can sleep well wherever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.98,0:16:36.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:40.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then could you go tell Clara and Ben\Nthat we don't need more?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.11,0:16:40.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.72,0:16:50.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad is bringing along that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.16,0:16:52.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's a large barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.63,0:17:01.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was lying on the shore over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.06,0:17:04.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom is gone, so it's won't be good\Nfor holding water any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:06.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you bring it here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:09.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That tent cannot accommodate us all sleeping in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.08,0:17:15.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, someone will have to sleep in here?\NDad, who will be sleeping here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.02,0:17:18.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Lucy, you want to sleep here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.62,0:17:19.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:21.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Scared to do it alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:22.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.96,0:17:25.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿But together with Kate, I'd be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:28.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you two could sleep here together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.23,0:17:31.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it would be better to let Ben sleep here instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.37,0:17:34.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿I wanna sleep here!\NAh, Kate is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.47,0:17:36.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.10,0:17:39.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We two will be sleeping in a barrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.81,0:17:41.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In a barrel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.23,0:17:43.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!\NLet me have that straw.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.88,0:17:47.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, the tent doesn't need any more straw, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:51.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well done. Please lay\Nthe remaining straw inside this barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.99,0:17:52.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Inside the barrel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.99,0:17:56.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Kate will sleep in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.66,0:17:58.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.13,0:18:01.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:04.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're still to hear what Kate says.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.60,0:18:14.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I {\i1}will{\i0} sleep here!﻿\NSleeping inside a barrel is a fantastic idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.49,0:18:16.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! May I have that straw?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.75,0:18:20.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here! Let me finish the bed for us! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.35,0:18:24.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, you are mean, mean, mean! Oh, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.72,0:18:29.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, shouldn't I sleep here instead of them?\NEveryone would feel easier this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.05,0:18:32.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Your mom said so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.53,0:18:36.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Leaving them together\Nin a place like this is a receipt for quarrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:37.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:39.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.12,0:18:42.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿We're sleeping in the barrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.68,0:19:33.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Before we proceed to eating,\Nthere's something I'd like to say to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.85,0:19:36.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from Tob,\Nwho probably won't understand a word of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.43,0:19:40.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want everyone to listen closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.16,0:19:45.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We have all made it safely to Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.57,0:19:48.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I trust you are all well aware of my goal here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:53.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,which is to build a farm much bigger\Nthan the one we had back in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.17,0:19:55.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to think it won't take too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.21,0:19:56.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But until that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.76,0:20:00.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want everyone to endure patiently\Nall the hardships we're to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:05.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we're not staying in this area forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:09.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow or the day after that,\NI'm going to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:13.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Adelaide is about ten kilometers\Ninwards from this shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.40,0:20:20.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The capital of Southern Australia, it's being erected as a glorious city that no one can be ashamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.10,0:20:23.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Once we finally make it to Adelaide,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.55,0:20:27.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll assemble a magnificent prefabricated home\Nwith the parts we brought from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.31,0:20:38.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so, once I buy a sizable plot,\Nwe could see it turn into a magnificent farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.76,0:20:46.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes my address.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.93,0:20:49.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, isn't everyone hungry? 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.84,0:20:56.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.54,0:21:03.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Here, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.07,0:21:06.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.58,0:21:12.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You never know what prowls the dead of night\Nwhile you sleep in that barrel. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.32,0:21:13.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿What do you think might prowl here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.72,0:21:16.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, the spirits of the dead will rise? 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.23,0:21:19.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a buffoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.14,0:21:24.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.99,0:21:30.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This place is still full of wild dogs.\NThey look like wolves and are ghastly for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.37,0:21:30.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:31.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.64,0:21:34.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿See? ﻿See? ﻿See?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.78,0:21:40.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You really are a buffoon.\NThat is Mr. Pettywell's black dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.25,0:21:46.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿That is bad manners!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.35,0:21:49.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have an urgent message for brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.02,0:21:51.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.06,0:21:55.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of what you say to Lucy-May,\Nshe is determined to sleep in the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.30,0:21:59.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Suit yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.35,0:22:53.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh? Marsh, what's the matter?\NYou'll get crushed down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.18,0:22:54.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go back into the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:12.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.67,0:23:13.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.51,0:23:17.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿Wake up! A strange animal\Njust came and looked at us!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.11,0:23:18.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Strange animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.45,0:23:22.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It kinda was like a rabbit,\Nbut an enormous one!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.12,0:23:24.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,﻿It was hop-hopping on two legs!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.32,0:23:29.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So a rabbit after all?\NGo back to sleep, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.79,0:23:34.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it's some kind of rabbit after all, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.33,0:23:40.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As we later found out, the animal Lucy-May saw
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.08,0:23:45.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,was an animal indigenous to Australia,\Nand only inhabiting it, called kangaroo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.72,0:23:52.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We never had any idea such an outlandish animal\Ncan even exist somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.13,0:24:10.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On our way back home from the creek,\Nwe found this adorable and docile animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.46,0:24:14.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"A Cute Fellow".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.28,0:24:15.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
